The out-of-scope features define the functionalities that are not included in CookSnap â€“ Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images.
These limitations help maintain a clear project boundary and prevent scope creep.

Out-of-Scope Features

Online Grocery Purchasing or Delivery
The system will not support online grocery ordering, payment processing, or home delivery services.

User Dietary Consultation or Medical Advice
Personalized health, nutrition, or medical recommendations are not provided.

Live Cooking Classes or Video Tutorials
Real-time cooking sessions or instructional videos are excluded.

Advanced Meal Planning and Scheduling
Weekly or monthly meal planning and reminders are not supported.

Integration with Smart Kitchen Appliances
The system will not connect with IoT devices or smart kitchen equipment.

Advanced Analytics and AI Predictions
Complex analytics such as calorie tracking, nutrition forecasting, or consumption prediction are not included.

Third-Party E-Commerce or Food Delivery Integration
Integration with external food delivery or e-commerce platforms is excluded.
